You have access to the PowerPoint presentation tool.

Capabilities:
- Create new presentations with slides containing titles, text, and bullet points
- Add and modify individual slides within existing presentations
- Read presentation content and metadata
- Export presentation structure

Best practices:
- Use concise, impactful text on slides (6x6 rule: max 6 bullets, max 6 words each)
- Start with an outline before creating slides
- Include a title slide, agenda, key content slides, and a summary/next-steps slide
- Use consistent formatting throughout the presentation

Output format:
- The tool returns JSON with slide content, metadata, and file path when applicable
- Specify the action explicitly: "create", "add_slide", "read", or "list_slides"
